title: For Sale:   GERMAN MODEL 1919 DWM LUGER
postcontent: A Very good condition German luger pistol in 7.65mm that is known as the Model 1919 "Commercial" made right after WWI by DWM. This gun is all matching numbered and falls into the correct serial range and does not have a chamber date. Pistol is serial #82591 and is NOT marked "germany" and does not have any import markings. It is estimated that about 13,000 guns were new made in this configuration before production resumed for the German military. Toggle has the DWM logo, chamber is undated and pistol has several crown "N" proofmarks. Action is smooth and functions fine. Bore is bright and excellent with strong rifling. Metal finish is original blue with some holster and much grip wear. Checkered walnut grips have a tight fit and are unmarked as is correct. Bright metal magazine fits and functions fine and is unumbered as is correct. A seldom seen DWM new built Model 1919 Commercial Luger.
